
// This Hyperlambda code sets the value of a [.token] node by concatenating the string "Bearer " with a configuration value retrieved using [config.get] for the key "magic:openai:key". The [set-value] slot assigns the concatenated result to [.token], effectively creating a Bearer token string for authorization purposes. The [strings.concat] slot combines the static string with the configuration value, which is expected to be an API key or similar credential.
set-value:x:@.token
   strings.concat
      .:"Bearer "
      config.get:"magic:openai:key"
